The paper discusses information-theoretically motivated approaches to statistical inference and model selection, which are relevant to several sub-fields of computer science. The use of Minimum Description Length (MDL) and Minimum Message Length (MML) principles suggests a focus on information theory and coding theory, which falls under the category of cs.IT. The paper also discusses predictive modeling, which is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The empirical results suggest that the methods are applied to small data sets, which is relevant to data science (cs.DS) and statistical inference (cs.SI).
